import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['precipitation'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.7, label='Precipitation')
    plt.axvline(data['precipitation'].median(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=2, label=f"Median: {data['precipitation'].median():.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Precipitation')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_max'], label='Max Temperature', color='red')
    plt.plot(data['date'], data['temp_min'], label='Min Temperature', color='blue')
    plt.xlabel('Date')
    plt.ylabel('Temperature (°C)')
    plt.title('How does temperature vary over time?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend()
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['wind'], data['precipitation'], alpha=0.5)
    plt.xlabel('Wind')
    plt.ylabel('Precipitation')
    plt.title('What is the relationship between wind and precipitation?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    weather_counts = data['weather'].value_counts()
    weather_counts.plot(kind='bar', color=['blue', 'orange', 'green', 'red', 'purple'])
    plt.xlabel('Weather Conditions')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the most common weather condition in Seattle?', wrap=True)
    plt.legend(weather_counts.index, title='Weather Conditions')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]

    fig, ax = plt.subplots(1, 2, figsize=(12, 6))
    data.boxplot(column='temp_max', by='weather', ax=ax[0])
    data.boxplot(column='temp_min', by='weather', ax=ax[1])

    ax[0].set_title('Max Temperature by Weather Condition')
    ax[1].set_title('Min Temperature by Weather Condition')
    fig.suptitle('How does temperature affect the weather condition?', wrap=True)
    plt.subplots_adjust(wspace=0.3)

    return plt

chart = plot(data)
